Couples Retreat is a   comedy film directed by Peter Billingsley and written by Jon Favreau, Vince Vaughn and Dana Fox.
Vaughn and Favreau star with Faizon Love, Jason Bateman, Kristin Davis, Kristen Bell, Malin Akerman and Jean Reno.
The film is rated PG-13 for sexual content and language.
It was released on October 9, 2009.
Plot
Jason (Jason Bateman) and Cynthia (Kristen Bell) are dangerously close to getting a divorce.
In a last ditch effort to save their marriage, they decide to take a vacation to a tropical resort meant to help ailing couples through therapy.
Short on cash, they enlist help from their friends to offset the cost through a group rate: the kid-raising Dave (Vince Vaughn) and Ronnie (Malin Akerman), the lovelessly married Joey (Jon Favreau) and Lucy (Kristen Davis), and the recently divorced Shane (Faizon Love) and his much younger girlfriend Trudy (Kali Hawk).
The three other couples think they are just going to have fun and help their friends, but they realize they are in for having their relationships examined as well.
